Our dataset has 4 variables, meaning there are 16 possible combinations of them if we are comparing two at a time. Messing around with that visualization to find a good line for all of the plots in this grid sure sounds tedious. Instead we make the computer do it for us. (For the real heads, this is a âœ³(em "generalized linear model")ðŸ”š)

So instead of repeatedly drawing one line 100 times, we're repeatedly drawing 16 lines 100 times each, each of which goes for N times, and so on. So we're making the computer do a lot more math pretty quickly.

